defaultThe policy objective behind this proposal is to deliver Professor Lofstedt's recommendation by exempting those self-employed who pose no potential risk of harm to others.
default&#xa0;
default&#xa0;
default&#xa0;
defaultIf the proposal is accepted, Section 3(2) of Health and Safety at Work etc Act 1974 (1974 Act)
default&#xa0;
defaultwill
default&#xa0;
defaultread:
default&#xa0;
default(2) It shall be the duty of every self-employed person who conducts a relevant undertaking to conduct the undertaking in such a way as to ensure, so far as is reasonably practicable, that he and other persons (not being his employees) who may be affected thereby are not thereby exposed to risks to their health and safety.
default(2A) For the purposes of subsection (2), an undertaking is a relevant undertaking if -
default(a) it is of a prescribed description, or
default(b) persons who may be affected by the way it is conducted, other than the person conducting it (or his employees), could thereby be exposed to risks to their health and safety.
default&#xa0;
defaultThe
default&#xa0;
defaultconsultation received responses from the following self-employed persons who classed themselves as businesses:
