defaultIt is recognised that workers in some occupations pose a risk of harm to others only at certain times.
default&#xa0;
default On practical grounds
default&#xa0;
defaultit was decided that only those self-employed persons whose work activities would not be expected to put others at risk at any point in the normal course of their work would be exempt, except, if they work in prescribed high hazard
